Middle Eastern carrier Qatar Airways is offering free transit visa and Doha hotel stay for its customers in its bid to lure more travellers. The airline is offering passengers the alternative of upgrading transit to a stay over where they can tour and stay free of charge in a Doha hotel while on their stop over. “This unique offer will allow them to extend their layover into a stayover, giving them the opportunity to experience the many delights Qatar has to offer,” said Qatar Airways Chief Commercial Officer Ehab Amin.Qatar is one of the fastest growing airlines in the world.  